src_content: 2009년 국가 중요 민속 문화재 제263호로 지정되었으며 ,9대 강정숙 종부는 종가의 온기를 이어 온 노력으로 대한민국 문화 유산상을 수상하기도 하였습니다 .광주 학생독립운동의 도화선이 된' 나주 댕기 머리 사건 '의 주인공인 박준채 , 박기옥 선생님의 집안으로 , 호남 지방의 의병 및 독립운동에 참여했으며 , 나주 지역의 각종 사회운동과 근대교육을 이끌었습니다 .
dst_content: The Nampa Historic House was designated as No. 263 of the National Important Folk Cultural Property in 2009. Kang Jeong-suk, the 9th head of the family, has been awareded the National Cultural Heritage Award for the continuation of the family's warm hearts. The family is descended from Park Jun-chae and Park Ki-ok, the main characters behind the "Naju Ponytail Harassment Incident," which in turn sparked the Gwangju Student Independence Movement. The family then participated in the righteous army and independence movements in the Honam region of Korea, and led various social movements and modern education movements in Naju city.

src_content: ‘ 돗 ’ - 제주의 방언으로 돼지를 뜻해요 .제주도에서는 가장 맛있는 돼지 생갈비를 돗갈비라고 부른 답니다 .육지에서는 귀한 돼지생갈비지만 제주는 도축과 가공의 용이함 덕분에 신선하고 질 좋은 돼지의 수급이 좋아요 . 친환경 농장의 가장 품질 좋은 돼지만을 빠르고 신선한 상태로 손님상에 올립니다 .
dst_content: Dot ' - The term in Jeju dialect means pork. In Jeju, the tastiest fresh pork ribs are called 'dotgalbi.' Although fresh pork ribs are rare in the mainland, Jeju cuisine is able to utilize fresh and high quality meat due to the convenience in the butchering and transportation processes. Only the highest quality pork from organic farms are allowed on the guest's tables in a quick manner and fresh state.

dst_content: A special traditional dish of Nampa House. The Park head family of Milyang, Naju, make the kimchi in October, when the paulownia leaves fall. The kimchi has always been served near the winter solstice after a fermentation process that takes over a fortnight. By adding 15 ingredients, such as apples, pears, chestnuts, etc, with whole cabbages, the kimchi is known for its refreshing and spicy taste.
